{"common":{"language":"Language","english":"English","chinese":"Chinese","account":"Account","profile":"Profile","logout":"Log out","menu":"Menu","open":"Open","close":"Close"},"header":{"nav":{"home":"Home","about":"About","courses":"Courses","events":"Events","partners":"Partners","donate":"Donate"},"tracks":{"aiTitle":"AI Course","aiDesc":"Learn machine learning, vision, and practical AI deployment.","robotTitle":"Robot Course","robotDesc":"Build, program, and control robots from hardware to behavior."}},"home":{"hero":{"title":"Build Future with AI and Robotics","subtitle":"Hands-on programs for students, families, and schools","description":"RobotX Education helps the next generation build confidence through engineering projects. From coding and sensing to autonomous systems, our courses turn abstract concepts into real products."},"ai":{"title":"AI Course Introduction","description":"Our AI course introduces core ideas in machine learning, computer vision, and model deployment through guided projects. Students train small models, analyze data, and ship practical AI features they can demonstrate."},"robot":{"title":"Robot Course Introduction","description":"Our robotics track blends design, electronics, and coding. Learners assemble robots, connect sensors and controllers, and program movement and decision-making in real environments."}},"courses":{"hero":{"title":"Learn Robotics. Learn AI. Embrace Future."},"robot":{"title":"Robot Courses","subtitle":"We teach robotics setup, manipulation, and secondary development for future-ready engineering skills.","items":{"originman":{"title":"OriginMan Humanoid Development","desc":"Humanoid robot setup, motion control, and development workflow template."}}},"ai":{"title":"AI Courses","subtitle":"We teach how to master AI tools and boost productivity in real project workflows.","items":{"openclaw":{"title":"OpenClaw AI Workflow","desc":"Practical AI tools and deployment learning path for students and creators."}}}},"courseTemplate":{"tocTitle":"Table of Contents","pagesTitle":"Course Pages","pagesButtonLabel":"Course Pages"},"openclaw":{"pages":{"home":"Home"},"title":"OpenClaw AI Course Template","intro":"This template is prepared for your upcoming tutorial content. Replace this text with your real lesson overview.","sections":{"setup":{"title":"Environment Setup","body":"Describe required tools, account setup, and prerequisites for learners.","subA":{"title":"Step 1: Install and Configure","body":"Add install links, version notes, and initial checks."},"subB":{"title":"Step 2: Verify Workspace","body":"Explain how learners can verify their local or cloud workspace is ready."}},"workflow":{"title":"Core AI Workflow","body":"Explain prompt design, model interaction, and iterative testing in this section.","subA":{"title":"Tool Integration","body":"Show how to connect AI output to real robot or software tasks."}},"practice":{"title":"Practice Project","body":"Add a hands-on mini project and evaluation checklist for students."}}},"originman":{"pages":{"home":"Home","quickStart":"Quick Start","userGuide":"User Guide"},"title":"OriginMan Robot Course","intro":"OriginMan is a future-oriented intelligent desktop humanoid robot and the first fully open-source ROS2 desktop humanoid robot project, aimed at letting every participant enjoy the fun of robot development.","sections":{"openSource":{"title":"Open Source Co-creation","body":"\"Open Sharing, Smart Future\" is OriginMan's evolutionary philosophy, looking forward to building the future of robotics with developers worldwide.","subA":{"title":"Open Source Ecosystem","body":"Providing source code for the control system, brain-cerebellum communication protocols, and motion editing software, helping every developer easily create their own \"intelligent brain,\" unleash unique creativity, and develop diverse applications."},"subB":{"title":"Continuous Iteration","body":"Fear not the endless pursuit of truth, for each step forward brings its own joy. Backed by strong community support, both OriginMan and its developers continue to progress, with ongoing hardware and software iterations and regular version updates, letting us grow stronger together."},"subC":{"title":"Comprehensive Content","body":"OriginMan is not just an open-source kit but your robotic friend. Complete with hardware, software, tutorials, video resources, and forum support, the rich software and hardware support helps you grow quickly."}},"evolution":{"title":"Intelligent Evolution Platform","body":"OriginMan is not just a hardware development platform but an evolving intelligent algorithm platform with unlimited possibilities.","subA":{"title":"Cognitive Core","body":"OriginMan natively carries the D-Robotics Development Board - RDK X5, with 10TOPS computing power supporting real-time visual inference and natural language processing. Pre-installed with a large model interaction system, it enables multi-turn dialogue understanding and AI intelligent interaction, offering a true intelligent robot development experience."},"subB":{"title":"Rich Applications","body":"OriginMan uses ROS2 and TogetheROS Bot (D-Robotics's deeply optimized ROS open-source robot operating system) as its robot software system, compatible with many applications in the ROS ecosystem, ready to use out of the box. Rich built-in applications allow quick start with human imitation learning, visual line following, AI voice interaction, and other application development."}},"secondaryDev":{"title":"Secondary Development","body":"Provide extension ideas for sensors, behaviors, and custom modules."}},"quickStart":{"title":"OriginMan Quick Start","intro":"Let's start using OriginMan!","sections":{"boot":{"title":"Power On","body":"(1) Turn on the main power switch. You can observe that the power light on OriginMan's back expansion board and the RDK X5 power indicator light up, while OriginMan's chest begins to glow white.\n\n(2) After waiting 10 seconds, you'll see OriginMan's chest light ring change from white to colorful, followed by OriginMan saying \"Hello, I'm OriginMan\". These actions indicate that OriginMan has successfully started up."},"remoteConnection":{"title":"Remote Connection","body":"(1) Launch MobaXterm and remotely log in to OriginMan\n\n(2) Enter username and password: root (username), root (password)\n\n(3) Remote login successful"},"example1":{"title":"Running Example (Dancing with the Robot)","body":"After having the robot imitate your actions, it's your turn to learn from the robot.\nAfter successful SSH connection, enter the following command to operate OriginMan:"},"poweroff":{"title":"Power Off","body":"If you need to shut down the robot, you can enter the following command in the terminal to close the software system:","body1":"After waiting about 5 seconds, you can turn off the power switch on the robot controller, and the robot shutdown is complete."}}},"userGuide":{"title":"OriginMan User Guide","intro":"During the following operations, you'll need some basic knowledge of robot development. We suggest you know the basic of python, linux, Ubuntu, ssh, ROS/ROS2 before proceed the following content.","sections":{"control":{"title":"Power On and Network Connection","body":"After opening your OriginMan package, you'll see the robot itself. Each OriginMan comes with its soul - the \"factory image.\"\n\nYou can start OriginMan by toggling the switch at the lower back of the robot.\n\nUpon successful startup, you'll see the chest light ring change from white to colorful, followed by OriginMan saying \"Hello, I'm OriginMan.\" This indicates the image has started successfully.\n\nOn OriginMan's back, if connected to a network, the Oled screen will display the IP address you need to connect to. If not connected, you'll need to connect an ethernet cable to configure networking between OriginMan and your local PC."},"runQuickStart":{"title":"Running Quick Start Examples","body":"Now you're ready to make OriginMan move. Follow the Quick Start Guide to complete OriginMan's first operation - let OriginMan dance with your movements!"}}}},"about":{"hero":{"title":"Why Families Choose RobotX","subtitle":"Understandable, intuitive, and inspiring learning experiences"},"reasons":{"title":"Why choose our courses","understandableTitle":"Understandable Learning","understandableDesc":"We break complex AI and robotics topics into clear steps that students can actually apply.","intuitiveTitle":"Intuitive Curriculum","intuitiveDesc":"Every lesson follows a practical build-first path, so learners see results quickly.","multimediaTitle":"Text, Images, and Video","multimediaDesc":"Our content combines short explanations, illustrative visuals, and hands-on demos."},"mission":{"title":"Our Mission","description":"Our mission is to help the next generation engage with the latest robotics and AI technology through practical education, creativity, and community impact."},"media":{"title":"Learn by Seeing and Building","description":"Students learn faster when they can read, watch, and build in the same lesson flow."}},"careers":{"hero":{"title":"Careers at RobotX","subtitle":"Join our nonprofit team and help students access future-ready education"},"openingsTitle":"Open Positions","card":{"title":"Event Operator Contractor","location":"San Francisco Bay Area, CA","type":"Contractor"},"details":{"title":"Event Operator Contractor","compensationLabel":"Compensation","compensationValue":"$30-$45/hour","jobTypeLabel":"Job Type","jobTypeValue":"Contractor","locationLabel":"Location","locationValue":"San Francisco Bay Area, CA","descriptionLabel":"Job Description","descriptionValue":"Support robotics and AI education events, coordinate logistics, set up learning stations, and assist students and families during workshops and school activities.","applyTitle":"Apply for this role","submit":"Submit Application","close":"Close"},"form":{"firstName":"First Name","lastName":"Last Name","email":"Email","resume":"Resume Attachment","whyUs":"Why us?","placeholderWhyUs":"Share why you want to work with RobotX and this role."}},"events":{"hero":{"title":"Community Events","subtitle":"Hands-on workshops, demos, and school collaborations"},"upcomingTitle":"Upcoming Events","cards":{"c1Title":"AI + Robotics Open Workshop","c1Meta":"San Jose, CA | Saturday","c1Desc":"Students and parents build mini robotics projects and experience AI demos.","c2Title":"School Outreach Demo Day","c2Meta":"Bay Area Schools | Weekday","c2Desc":"Our instructors visit partner schools to run engaging technology sessions."}},"donation":{"hero":{"title":"Donate","subtitle":"Help us bring robotics learning to more students"},"content":{"title":"Donate Robots to Schools and Universities","description":"We are not yet set up with Stripe. If you would like to donate robots, kits, or equipment to schools, colleges, or universities through our nonprofit, please contact us directly at info@usrobotx.com."}},"partners":{"hero":{"title":"Become a Partner","subtitle":"Collaborate with us to educate the younger generation"},"content":{"title":"Partnership Opportunities","description":"We partner with schools, companies, and community organizations to expand access to AI and robotics education through programs, events, and resources."}},"footer":{"contact-us":"Contact Us","phone":"Phone: 800-519-0881","email":"Email: info@usrobotx.com","copyright":"© 2026 Robot Education Initiative"},"auth":{"login":"Log in","loginTitle":"Log in","loginSubtitle":"Welcome back to RobotX.","loginAction":"Log in","signupAction":"Sign up","resetPasswordTitle":"Reset your password","resetPasswordSubtitle":"Use the link from your email to set a new password.","newPassword":"New password","confirmPassword":"Confirm password","resetAction":"Update password","passwordsMismatch":"Passwords do not match.","resetSessionMissing":"Your reset session is missing. Please open the link from your email again.","resetFailed":"Password reset failed.","